{"type":"message","id":"9dc75907","parentId":"000ac0c9","timestamp":"2026-04-14T16:19:43.693Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me analyze the active sessions (excluding this cron session):\n\n1. `agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:group:-5163901258` - status: running, startedAt: 1776163408296 (about 3h 30min ago from 16:18 UTC), last message was \"HEARTBEAT_OK\" at 16:08 UTC\n2. `agent:master-orchestrator:cron:6f3323ef-607e-42a0-b946-611913081d31` - status: running, startedAt: 1776152701090 (about 2h 48min ago from 16:18 UTC)\n\n\n3. `agent:master-orchestrator:cron:ed2d0b5d-fc56-42eb-a8fc-973a48024df7` - status: running, startedAt: 1776180724499 (about 1h 50min ago from 16:18 UTC)\n4. `agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:direct:6053576134` - status: done (ended ~14min ago), so I'll skip reporting this one\n5. `agent:master-orchestrator:main` - also status: done\n\n, so I'm excluding it as well\n\nThe cron:e7885813-0446-4101-a171-941c2416848e session is the one this cron job is running in, so that gets excluded too. So I'm left with just those three running sessions: the QLHV Telegram group, the 5p Progress Report cron job for DTLX, and the regular 5p Progress Report cron job. Now I need to figure out what each one is actually doing based on their session data. The QLHV Telegram group session ended around 16:09 UTC based on the last message timestamp, which means it wasn't actually running when I did the baseline check at 15:30 UTC.\n\nWait, I'm seeing conflicting information here—the session list shows it as \"running\" but the last message was sent at 16:11 UTC, yet the endedAt timestamp is 16:09 UTC. I think what happened is the session ended naturally after sending that HEARTBEAT_OK message, and then a new cron job spawned to check on it, creating this inconsistency where the status appears stuck as \"running\" even though the session has actually terminated. So the status might actually be misleading—the session could have ended around 16:09 UTC when the last message was sent, but OpenClaw's state tracking hasn't caught up yet. Looking at the other cron jobs in the list, they're all showing \"running\" status, which suggests they genuinely are still active.\n\nNow I'm seeing a new cron job started at 16:12 UTC and is currently running—that's the one I'm in right now. The 5p Progress Report cron ran every 5 minutes and sent messages to both webchat and the telegram group, which is a different pattern than the Agent Status cron.\n\nI need to figure out what each session is actually doing by looking at their labels and child sessions. The cron:e7885813-0446-4101-a171-941c2416848e session is labeled \"Cron: Agent Status to Lead\" but it started at 16:12 UTC, which is odd because I thought the previous cron instance ended at 16:13 UTC—so there's something off with the timing here.\n\nActually, I think the current cron session is the new instance spawned by the cron scheduler, and it's labeled as the Agent Status cron because that's the job it's running. So the real sessions I should be reporting are the three that are actually running right now: the telegram group session for the QLHV ecosystem, the cron session for the 5p Progress Report DTLX, and the cron session for the 5p Progress Report itself.\n\nBut I'm noticing something odd about the telegram group session—the last message is from 16:08 UTC and the session has been running for about 5 hours, but it's showing as \"running\" even though a cron job just sent a heartbeat to it. This seems like a stale session that's still showing as active in the orchestrator even though it's not really doing anything anymore. The endedAt timestamp shows 16:09 UTC, but the last message timestamp is 16:11 UTC—there's definitely some inconsistency here. Rather than getting stuck on this, I'll just report what the session list actually shows: the QLHV group is marked as running and it's been active for about 5 hours based on the start time. I'm calculating the duration from the start time of 1776163408296 ms, which comes out to roughly 5 hours and 49 minutes from 16:18 UTC. So that's 10:29 AM + 5:49 = 4:18 PM. ✓\n\nActually, that seems way too long for the QLHV group. Let me recalculate using timestamps instead. The startedAt timestamp of 1776163408296 ms converts to April 14, 2026 at 10:29:44 UTC, and since the current time is 16:18 UTC on the same date, that's a 5 hour 48 minute gap—which would put us at 4:18 PM UTC+7. But that feels too long. Let me reconsider whether I'm looking at the right timestamp or if there's something else going on with the start time. Looking at the session metadata, the startedAt timestamp of 1776163408296 converts to 10:29:44 UTC on April 14, 2026, which puts the current time at 4:18 PM—that's a 5 hour 49 minute difference, confirming the runtime duration is accurate.\n\nBut I'm noticing the endedAt timestamp shows the session as completed at 16:09 UTC, yet it's still marked as running in the status, which seems contradictory. I suspect the session actually ended and OpenClaw spawned a new instance to keep it running, which would explain the discrepancy between the endedAt time and the current status.\n\nLooking at the session data more carefully, the child sessions that were spawned are all listed as completed, and the last message was just a heartbeat response, so this QLHV group session appears to be in a stale running state even though it should have ended. I'm going to trust the status field as the source of truth here and move forward with compiling the report.\n\nSo I've identified three active sessions to report on: the QLHV group session which is running but likely stale, a 5p Progress Report cron job for DTLX that's been running for about 2 hours 48 minutes, and a 5p Progress Report cron job that's been running for roughly 2 hours. Since I'm not sure what the QLHV group is actively doing at this moment, I'll note its general purpose based on the session context. Then I'll send this compiled report to Lead.","thinkingSignature":"ba15cbd29c62fa5abf46e2d024c0a3dececbc1d39222f8df2f0f9a08bda35ad4"},{"type":"text","text":"Now let me compile the report from the session data:\n- Current time: 16:18 UTC\n- Excluding this cron session: `agent:master-orchestrator:cron:e7885813-0446-4101-a171-941c2416848e`\n- Active (status=running): 3 sessions\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_lnvcka9407jp_1","name":"sessions_send","arguments":{"sessionKey":"agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:direct:6053576134","message":"🌐 Orbis — Agent Status | 16:18 UTC 14 Apr\n\nActive sessions: 3\n• telegram:group:-5163901258: running — QLHV Ecosystem group monitor (last heartbeat: ~16:08 UTC) — ~5h 49m\n• cron:6f3323ef (DTLX): running — 5p Progress Report → DTLX group — ~2h 48m\n• cron:ed2d0b5d: running — 5p Progress Report → QLHV group — ~1h 51m\n\nNote: telegram:-5163901258 session endedAt logged at 16:09 UTC but status shows running — likely awaiting new activity."}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":5422,"output":1696,"cacheRead":13849,"cacheWrite":310,"totalTokens":21277,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776183552529,"responseId":"062d9c0180e08778cf9f828ef2ff19da"}}
